   <head>The Printer to the curteous Reader.</head>
   <p>IN perusing this book, if thou find any faults which haue es<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>caped in the printing, I pray thee to correct them with thy Pen. Afterwards reade the book thoroughly, and belieue me no more, if thou find not therein sufficient cause te thinke thy labour well bestowed:</p>
